article.headline: Lehigh 60, Columbia 57
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Jose Olivero made a 3-pointer with 6 seconds left to help Lehigh salvage a 60-57 victory over Columbia after the Mountain Hawks blew a 15-point second-half lead Monday night. Columbia had a final chance to tie when Maurice Murphy was fouled on a desperation shot with less than a second left, but he missed all three of his free throws. Lehigh (4-3) scored the first four points of the second half to take a 36-21 lead, but the Lions (1-3) then went on a 24-0 run to make it 45-36 with 10:15 to play. Olivero, who finished with 23 points, then led a Lehigh rally that tied the score at 49. With Lehigh leading 57-54, Columbia's Matt Preston hit a layup and foul shot with 29 seconds left to forge the fourth tie of the second half. But 23 seconds later, Olivero sank his 25-footer. Lehigh led 32-21 at halftime but Columbia used a full-court press to force six turnovers and began its 24-0 run with Dragutin Kravic's layup with 18:35 to play and scored 20 points in the next 5:11, nine of them from Chris Owens and four more from Matt Land. Kravic was the only Lions player in double figures, finishing with 10. Austen Rowland added 10 for the Mountain Hawks, who have won three in a row.
